## What Guardrails are for

A Guardrail is a **prohibition statement**: "the business will
not do X." Each Guardrail captures one of {{PRINCIPAL_NAME}}'s core
values, expressed as a line the business won't cross — even in
pursuit of the Outcomes in `Goals.md`.

Each Guardrail has 1-3 SMART Interim Guardrails — leading
indicators that the Guardrail is being honored in practice — and
1-5 Guardrail-aligned Initiatives that produce the honoring
behavior.

**Where Guardrails are loaded:**

- **Sentinel** (spec §5) — the read-only watchdog. Reads
  Guardrails.md at session boundaries to know what to flag.
- **AnalystJudge / Audit** (spec §7) — the weekly audit reads
  Guardrails.md to surface drift (Initiatives that are crossing
  lines, Interim Guardrails that aren't being honored).
- **Send-guard** (spec §6.4) — outbound mail gate reads
  Guardrails.md to flag messages that violate prohibitions.

**Where Guardrails are NOT loaded:**

- Skill prompts at `pre_llm_call` — the agency generates work in
  service of `Goals.md` (aim, always present). Guardrails are
  checked *after* the work is generated, not woven into every
  turn's prompt. Putting Guardrails in the always-loaded context
  would bias the agency toward defensive thinking instead of
  aimed work.

